						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is in characters of the 17th century A.D. and records a gift of the groves of <hi rend="italic">iluppai</hi> and mango trees for the purpose of providing sacred bath to the image of the god Koḻundiśurasvāmi by Vaittiyanāthadēvar, son of Muttadēvar and Vaittiyanāthadēvar, son of Malaiyadēvar, for the merit of Siṅgapperumāḷ.</p>						

						</summary>
